Review: The place gets too crowded in the evening. The kiosk takes a long time to recognize if you are a regular. There are so many customers that the staff can't clean the tables. Also, they ran out of sauce and didn't refill it. The hamburger is basically a Big Mac, but the patty seems to have been microwaved and the burger size is a bit small. But on the plus side, it's a bit cheaper than in Korea.
